<subSubSection pageId="14" pageNumber="15" type="diagnosis">
<paragraph blockId="14.[264,1325,283,1276]" pageId="14" pageNumber="15">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[312,439,283,309]" pageId="14" pageNumber="15">Diagnosis.</emphasis>
Male sternite 
<number box="[606,621,284,310]" pageId="14" pageNumber="15" value="6.0">6</number>
with short mesal notch, sternite 
<number box="[999,1014,284,310]" pageId="14" pageNumber="15" value="7.0">7</number>
strongly lobose, aedeagus mesally sculptured, gonostyle absent. Sternite 
<number box="[839,853,324,350]" pageId="14" pageNumber="15" value="7.0">7</number>
deeply lobose. Female T 
<number box="[1175,1188,324,350]" pageId="14" pageNumber="15" value="8.0">8</number>
+ 
<number box="[1205,1219,324,350]" pageId="14" pageNumber="15" value="9.0">9</number>
without mesal tooth­like projection.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection lastPageId="15" lastPageNumber="16" pageId="14" pageNumber="15" type="description">
<paragraph blockId="14.[264,1325,283,1276]" box="[312,457,403,429]" pageId="14" pageNumber="15">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[312,457,403,429]" pageId="14" pageNumber="15">Description</emphasis>
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="14.[264,1325,283,1276]" pageId="14" pageNumber="15">
<emphasis box="[312,380,444,469]" italics="true" pageId="14" pageNumber="15">Male.</emphasis>
Measurements (in mm). Body length, 2.04; wing length, 1.68; wing width, 0.70. Color. Dark brown specimens, mouthparts ochre­yellowish, antennae ochre. Thoracic sclerites ochre, scutum slightly darker; legs brownish ochre, except light ochre tarsi. Wings translucent, except brownish veins, medial and cubital veins lighter. Tergites brown, sternites light brown. Terminalia brown. Head. Flagellum with 
<number box="[1096,1111,604,630]" pageId="14" pageNumber="15" value="8.0">8</number>
flagellomeres, no sensory pit on maxillary palpus (
<figureCitation box="[668,759,644,670]" captionStart="FIGURE 20" captionStartId="14.[264,368,1719,1743]" captionText="FIGURE 20. Anapausis clivicola. Maxillary palpus." pageId="14" pageNumber="15">
Fig. 
<number box="[726,759,644,670]" pageId="14" pageNumber="15" value="20.0">20</number>
</figureCitation>
), no setae on front dorsal to antennae, palpus large, frontoclypeal setae present. Thorax (
<figureCitation box="[767,855,684,710]" captionStart="FIGURE 21" captionStartId="15.[264,368,1510,1534]" captionTargetBox="[284,1301,704,1473]" captionTargetId="figure@15.[284,1301,704,1473]" captionTargetPageId="15" captionText="FIGURE 21. Anapausis clivicola. Thorax, lateral view." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/173636/files/figure.png" pageId="14" pageNumber="15">
Fig. 
<number box="[822,855,684,710]" pageId="14" pageNumber="15" value="21.0">21</number>
</figureCitation>
): antepronotal setae, 
<number box="[1104,1137,684,710]" pageId="14" pageNumber="15" value="34.0">34</number>
; proepisternals, 
<number box="[264,311,724,750]" pageId="14" pageNumber="15" value="6.0" valueMax="7.0" valueMin="5.0">5–7</number>
; proepimerals, 
<number box="[492,509,724,750]" pageId="14" pageNumber="15" value="7.0">7</number>
; spiracular sclerite setae, 
<number box="[812,874,724,750]" pageId="14" pageNumber="15" value="8.5" valueMax="10.0" valueMin="7.0">7–10</number>
; anepisternals, 
<number box="[1055,1116,724,750]" pageId="14" pageNumber="15" value="13.0" valueMax="17.0" valueMin="9.0">9–17</number>
/ 
<number box="[1125,1138,724,750]" pageId="14" pageNumber="15" value="8.0">8</number>
; katepisternals, 
<number box="[264,311,764,790]" pageId="14" pageNumber="15" value="6.5" valueMax="7.0" valueMin="6.0">6–7</number>
; mesepimerals, 
<number box="[530,576,764,790]" pageId="14" pageNumber="15" value="4.5" valueMax="5.0" valueMin="4.0">4–5</number>
/ 
<number box="[586,599,764,790]" pageId="14" pageNumber="15" value="3.0">3</number>
; merals, 
<number box="[735,782,764,790]" pageId="14" pageNumber="15" value="2.5" valueMax="3.0" valueMin="2.0">2–3</number>
; subspiraculars, 
<number box="[1007,1055,764,790]" pageId="14" pageNumber="15" value="4.5" valueMax="5.0" valueMin="4.0">4–5</number>
; supra­alars, 
<number box="[1240,1315,764,790]" pageId="14" pageNumber="15" value="10.5" valueMax="11.0" valueMin="10.0">10–11</number>
; pedicelars, 
<number box="[400,415,804,830]" pageId="14" pageNumber="15" value="1.0">1</number>
; a number of longer scutellar setae not in regular row. Epimeron I sclerite rather large. Anteroventral edge of anepisternum with distinctive suture. Meral sclerite and episternum III of similar sizes. Wing. No ventral setae on any vein. M 
<number box="[1082,1090,900,914]" pageId="14" pageNumber="15" value="1.0">1</number>
incomplete basally, beginning rather close to Rs. Setae dorsally on all veins, except A 
<number box="[1096,1104,943,957]" pageId="14" pageNumber="15" value="1.0">1</number>
, which is shortly produced. Wing membrane bare on cell m 
<number box="[770,781,970,996]" pageId="14" pageNumber="15" value="1.0">1</number>
, cell m 
<number box="[869,883,970,996]" pageId="14" pageNumber="15" value="2.0">2</number>
with 
<number box="[951,966,970,996]" pageId="14" pageNumber="15" value="2.0">2</number>
macrotrichia, 
<number box="[1139,1183,970,996]" pageId="14" pageNumber="15" value="4.5" valueMax="5.0" valueMin="4.0">4–5</number>
on cell m 
<number pageId="14" pageNumber="15" value="4.14">4, 14</number>
on anal lobe (
<figureCitation box="[475,567,1010,1036]" captionStart="FIGURE 22" captionStartId="15.[264,367,1880,1904]" captionText="FIGURE 22. Anapausisclivicola. Wing." pageId="14" pageNumber="15">
Fig. 
<number box="[534,567,1010,1036]" pageId="14" pageNumber="15" value="22.0">22</number>
</figureCitation>
). Abdomen: Sternite 
<number box="[829,844,1010,1036]" pageId="14" pageNumber="15" value="1.0">1</number>
nearly unsclerotized. Pretergite 
<number box="[1238,1253,1010,1036]" pageId="14" pageNumber="15" value="2.0">2</number>
as in other species of genus. Male terminalia (
<figureCitation box="[736,823,1050,1076]" captionStart="FIGURE 23" captionStartId="16.[264,368,1167,1191]" captionTargetBox="[388,1210,331,1151]" captionTargetId="figure@16.[388,1210,326,1157]" captionTargetPageId="16" captionText="FIGURE 23. Anapausis clivicola. Male terminalia, ventral view." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/173637/files/figure.png" pageId="14" pageNumber="15">
Fig. 
<number box="[790,823,1050,1076]" pageId="14" pageNumber="15" value="23.0">23</number>
</figureCitation>
). S 
<number box="[859,874,1050,1076]" pageId="14" pageNumber="15" value="6.0">6</number>
with mesal posterior notch and pair of short projections; T 
<number box="[512,526,1090,1116]" pageId="14" pageNumber="15" value="6.0">6</number>
unmodified; S 
<number box="[718,733,1090,1116]" pageId="14" pageNumber="15" value="7.0">7</number>
reduced to pair of large lateral setose lobes, connected by slender, bare sclerotized strip; T 
<number box="[860,874,1130,1156]" pageId="14" pageNumber="15" value="7.0">7</number>
slightly rounded posteriorly; S 
<number box="[1276,1290,1130,1156]" pageId="14" pageNumber="15" value="8.0">8</number>
+ 
<number box="[1307,1322,1130,1156]" pageId="14" pageNumber="15" value="9.0">9</number>
apparently reduced to slender ventral strip, Gc and Gs unrecognizable as distinct plates; T 
<number box="[283,296,1210,1236]" pageId="14" pageNumber="15" value="8.0">8</number>
+ 
<number box="[313,327,1210,1236]" pageId="14" pageNumber="15" value="9.0">9</number>
well developed, with pair of spiracles; vesica small, aedeagus body sculptured, tubular distally; parameres well produced, with ventral sclerotized projection.
</paragraph>
<caption box="[264,827,1719,1743]" pageId="14" pageNumber="15">
<paragraph blockId="14.[264,827,1719,1743]" box="[264,827,1719,1743]" pageId="14" pageNumber="15">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[264,408,1719,1743]" pageId="14" pageNumber="15">FIGURE 20.</emphasis>
<taxonomicName box="[414,624,1720,1743]" class="Insecta" family="Scatopsidae" genus="Anapausis" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="14" pageNumber="15" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="clivicola">
<emphasis box="[414,624,1720,1743]" italics="true" pageId="14" pageNumber="15">
Anapausis 
<taxonomicName box="[532,624,1720,1743]" pageId="14" pageNumber="15" rank="species" species="clivicola">clivicola</taxonomicName>
</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
. Maxillary palpus.
</paragraph>
</caption>
<paragraph blockId="14.[264,1325,1789,1895]" lastBlockId="15.[264,1324,284,654]" lastPageId="15" lastPageNumber="16" pageId="14" pageNumber="15">
<emphasis box="[312,407,1789,1814]" italics="true" pageId="14" pageNumber="15">Female.</emphasis>
As for male except as follows. Measurements (in mm). Body length, 2.32; wing length, 1.88; wing width, 0.74. Thorax. Antepronotals, 
<number box="[1058,1091,1829,1855]" pageId="14" pageNumber="15" value="24.0">24</number>
; propisternals, 
<number box="[1288,1319,1829,1855]" pageId="14" pageNumber="15" value="11.0">11</number>
; spiracular sclerite setae, 
<number box="[554,571,1869,1895]" pageId="14" pageNumber="15" value="9.0">9</number>
; anepisterals, 
<number box="[739,769,1869,1895]" pageId="14" pageNumber="15" value="15.0">15</number>
/ 
<number box="[780,794,1869,1895]" pageId="14" pageNumber="15" value="8.0">8</number>
; katepisternals, 
<number box="[984,1016,1869,1895]" pageId="14" pageNumber="15" value="16.0">16</number>
; mesepimerals, 
<number box="[1206,1223,1869,1895]" pageId="14" pageNumber="15" value="9.0">9</number>
; merals, 
<number box="[264,281,284,310]" pageId="15" pageNumber="16" value="4.0">4</number>
; subspiraculars, 
<number box="[477,494,284,310]" pageId="15" pageNumber="16" value="6.0">6</number>
; supra­alars, 
<number box="[651,668,284,310]" pageId="15" pageNumber="16" value="6.0">6</number>
; no macrotrichia on cell m 
<number box="[990,1029,284,310]" pageId="15" pageNumber="16" value="1.2">1, 2</number>
on M 
<number box="[1102,1158,284,310]" pageId="15" pageNumber="16" value="2.12">2, 12</number>
on m 
<number box="[1228,1285,284,310]" pageId="15" pageNumber="16" value="4.2">4, 20</number>
on cuA 
<number box="[314,328,324,350]" pageId="15" pageNumber="16" value="2.0">2</number>
and anal lobe. Female terminalia as in 
<figureCitation box="[786,928,324,350]" captionStart="FIGURES 24, 25" captionStartId="16.[264,382,1695,1719]" captionTargetBox="[285,1285,1247,1669]" captionTargetId="figure@16.[283,1304,1245,1672]" captionTargetPageId="16" captionText="FIGURES 24, 25. Anapausis clivicola. Female terminalia. 24. Ventral view. 25. Dorsal view." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/173638/files/figure.png" pageId="15" pageNumber="16">
Figs. 
<number box="[851,928,324,350]" pageId="15" pageNumber="16" value="24.25">24, 25</number>
</figureCitation>
.
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="15.[264,1324,284,654]" pageId="15" pageNumber="16">
The presence of a pair of setose lobes laterally on S 
<number box="[957,971,364,390]" pageId="15" pageNumber="16" value="8.0">8</number>
is a very distinctive feature, shared only with 
<taxonomicName box="[467,582,401,426]" class="Insecta" family="Scatopsidae" genus="Anapausis" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="15" pageNumber="16" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="mourei" status="sp. nov.">
<emphasis box="[467,582,401,426]" italics="true" pageId="15" pageNumber="16">A. mourei</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
<emphasis bold="true" box="[589,683,401,427]" pageId="15" pageNumber="16">
<taxonomicNameLabel box="[589,683,401,427]" pageId="15" pageNumber="16" rank="species">sp. nov.</taxonomicNameLabel>
</emphasis>
As far as we are aware of, there is no other 
<taxonomicName box="[1200,1322,401,426]" class="Insecta" family="Scatopsidae" genus="Anapausis" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="15" pageNumber="16" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[1200,1322,401,426]" italics="true" pageId="15" pageNumber="16">Anapausis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
species with these setose lobes on S 
<number box="[715,730,439,465]" pageId="15" pageNumber="16" value="8.0">8</number>
, as is true also for other genera, making this a possible synapomorphy for the clade with this pair of species. There are no evident gonapophyses 
<number box="[437,452,513,539]" pageId="15" pageNumber="16" value="8.0">8</number>
on the terminalia, unlike in 
<taxonomicName box="[783,909,513,538]" class="Insecta" family="Scatopsidae" genus="Anapausis" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="15" pageNumber="16" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="mayana" status="sp. nov.">
<emphasis box="[783,909,513,538]" italics="true" pageId="15" pageNumber="16">A. mayana</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
<emphasis bold="true" box="[916,1010,513,539]" pageId="15" pageNumber="16">
<taxonomicNameLabel box="[916,1010,513,539]" pageId="15" pageNumber="16" rank="species">sp. nov.</taxonomicNameLabel>
</emphasis>
and 
<taxonomicName box="[1067,1170,513,538]" class="Insecta" family="Scatopsidae" genus="Anapausis" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="15" pageNumber="16" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="wirthi" status="sp. nov.">
<emphasis box="[1067,1170,513,538]" italics="true" pageId="15" pageNumber="16">A. wirthi</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
<emphasis bold="true" box="[1177,1270,513,539]" pageId="15" pageNumber="16">
<taxonomicNameLabel box="[1177,1270,513,539]" pageId="15" pageNumber="16" rank="species">sp. nov.</taxonomicNameLabel>
</emphasis>
, but as in 
<taxonomicName box="[326,486,551,576]" class="Insecta" family="Scatopsidae" genus="Anapausis" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="15" pageNumber="16" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="fuscinervis">
<emphasis box="[326,486,551,576]" italics="true" pageId="15" pageNumber="16">A. fuscinervis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection pageId="15" pageNumber="16" type="etymology">
<paragraph blockId="15.[264,1324,284,654]" pageId="15" pageNumber="16">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[312,445,587,613]" pageId="15" pageNumber="16">Etymology</emphasis>
